{"type":"HOSTEL","name":"Junohall YHA Hostel Waitomo","nameEN":"Junohall YHA Hostel Waitomo","isActive":true,"isNew":false,"description":"Nestled within rolling hills and private farmland, Juno Hall provides a countryside feeling while still being located within 2kms of the Waitomo Glow Worm Caves. Waitomo Village is 1.5km, or a 10-15min walk down the road. We feature amenities such as a tennis court and an outdoor swimming pool, which is delightful in the summertime. The accommodation provides a large shared kitchen, shared bathroom facilities and free unlimited WiFi for all guests. We offer an outdoor barbecue for guests to use if they wish. As well as enjoying the caving experiences the various companies have to offer, you will be able to enjoy activities around Waitomo Caves, such as beautiful hikes/bush walks throughout the unique landscape and native forests. Otorohanga and Te Kuiti are the closest towns to us, 16km either way. We advise that you bring food with you if you do not have transport as there is no supermarket in Waitomo (but lovely local restaurants if you wish to treat yourself). We are happy to collect guests arriving via bus from the Village bus stops if required, just call on the day and we will pick you up! The nearest airport is Hamilton Airport, 63 km from the accommodation. Auckland Airport is approx 2.5hrs drive from us, Rotorua and Taupo approx 2hrs and New Plymouth approx 2.5hrs.\n\nBed and Room Movements\n\nWhilst every endeavour will be made to ensure you are accommodated in the same room throughout your stay, due to limited availability at time of booking, it may be necessary for you to change rooms. If applicable, you will be advised of this at check-in. You will be accommodated in a room of similar or higher standard to that originally booked. \nDue to limited availability at time of booking, multi-share accommodation for two or more guests may be provided in separate rooms. Every endeavour will be made to ensure this does not occur